STATE of Iowa, Appellee,
v.
William E. CRAWFORD, Appellant. No. 17-1640 Supreme Court of Iowa. Filed April 26, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION

A defendant appeals his conviction and sentence for second-degree murder. DECISION OF COURT OF APPEALS AFFIRMED IN PART AND VACATED IN PART; JUDGMENT OF CONVICTION AFFIRMED, SENTENCE VACATED IN PART, AND CASE REMANDED.

DECISION OF COURT OF APPEALS AFFIRMED IN PART. VACATED IN PART. JUDGMENT OF CONVICTION AFFIRMED. SENTENCE VACATED IN PART. CASE REMANDED.
